a home to an abandoned child.

74
00:04:52,663 --> 00:04:54,885
Shall I get Mrs. Campbell
on the line?

75
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:57,817
Just get me Bert Peterson.

76
00:05:02,444 --> 00:05:03,894
Well, hello, there.

77
00:05:04,256 --> 00:05:05,742
Hello, Bertram.

78
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:08,260
Is Florence with you?

79
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:10,395
No. She's taking care
of her mother.

80
00:05:10,818 --> 00:05:14,018
Then we were thinking about going to
the Breakers through New Year's.

81
00:05:14,475 --> 00:05:16,568
She's a good companion, isn't she?

82
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,613
She's moody.

83
00:05:20,068 --> 00:05:22,502
Damn it, Alice.
I don't ask much of you...

84
00:05:22,985 --> 00:05:25,635
My stockings cost more
than your carpeting.

85
00:05:27,541 --> 00:05:29,574
