you were undecided.

95
00:05:58,641 --> 00:06:00,028
What's your hesitation?

96
00:06:00,383 --> 00:06:03,282
I promised to take care of Roger.

97
00:06:03,818 --> 00:06:06,785
Let Roger Sterling have
what he always wanted...

98
00:06:06,905 --> 00:06:09,539
to die in the arms
of a 20-year-old.

99
00:06:10,171 --> 00:06:12,249
The truth is
you don't want to retire,

100
00:06:12,716 --> 00:06:14,823
and I hate to say this, Bertram,

101
00:06:14,943 --> 00:06:16,293
but you are old...

102
00:06:16,882 --> 00:06:18,040
older than me.

103
00:06:18,509 --> 00:06:20,717
I can't even imagine
what that must be like.

104
00:06:21,694 --> 00:06:22,694
Charming.

105
00:06:23,132 --> 00:06:25,284
Please. You're not well.

106
00:06:26,255 --> 00:06:28,182
This is what I do.

107
00:06:28,343 --> 00:06:30,810
It's a ***,
you can continue to do it.

108
00:06:31,046 --> 00:06:33,396
I'll be as useful
as the Queen of England.

109
00:06:33,803 --> 00:06:35,853
Don't you want to go to Montana?

110
00:06:36,178 --> 00:06:38,628
You ruined that poor
architect's life.

111
00:06:39,177 --> 00:06:40,694
Go visit your cattle.

112
00:06:41,994 --> 00:06:43,364
I do love them.

113
00:06:45,679 --> 00:06:47,769
But you can't trust the Brits.

114
00:07:08,114 --> 00:07:09,639
I've left a letter on my bureau.

115
00:07:10,403 --> 00:07:12,940
If I'm not back in two days,
the police will be here.

116
00:07:13,332 --> 00:07:14,746
Why would you bring that up?

117
00:07:14,866 --> 00:07:16,875
Because I don't
want you to hurt me.

118
00:07:17,975 --> 00:07:20,182
I just want to know
where my husband is.

119
00:07:20,461 --> 00:07:23,112
It's a simple misunderstanding.
There's a lot of men with my name.

120
00:07:23,453 --> 00:07:25,364
You're the only one who used
my husband's serial number

121
00:07:25,484 --> 00:07:27,069
to get a driver's license.

122
00:07:27,767 --> 00:07:29,451
Car title. Apartment lease.

123
00:07:29,762 --> 00:07:31,329
Do you have a birth certificate?

124
00:07:32,409 --> 00:07:34,499
- In a safe deposit box.
- Will you stop?

125
00:07:35,826 --> 00:07:37,334
I saw the look on your face.

126
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:40,254
I don't know what to say.
There's been a mistake.

127
00:07:40,556 --> 00:07:42,406
Can't you be a human being?

128
00:07:43,364 --> 00:07:44,475
I'm his wife.

129
00:07:45,524 --> 00:07:47,804
I don't care what he asked you to do.
I need to know.

130
00:07:48,547 --> 00:07:51,083
- I have to get back to work.
- Stop lying.

131
00:07:52,274 --> 00:07:53,350
You've been caught.

132
00:07:53,930 --> 00:07:56,255
Don't make me do something
I don't want to do.

133
00:08:02,241 --> 00:08:03,241
He died.

134
00:08:04,679 --> 00:08:05,738
I'm sorry.

135
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:07,430
What?

136
00:08:10,053 --> 00:08:10,992
I'm sorry.

137
00:08:12,117 --> 00:08:13,286
Are you sure?

138
00:08:28,203 --> 00:08:29,953
He never said he had a wife.

139
00:08:31,192 --> 00:08:32,303
Seven years.

140
00:08:43,931 --> 00:08:45,540
I'm very, very sorry.

141
00:08:46,118 --> 00:08:47,405
What happened?

142
00:08:48,249 --> 00:08:49,823
He was killed in combat.

143
00:08:50,991 --> 00:08:52,160
So who are you?

144
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:56,100
They thought I was him
and he was me.

145
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:58,748
I didn't think
I was hurting anyone.

146
00:09:00,306 --> 00:09:01,756
I can't believe it.

147
00:09:03,525 --> 00:09:05,213
I just had to get out of there.

148
00:09:08,334 --> 00:09:10,135
What are you going to do to me?

149
00:09:11,515 --> 00:09:13,147
He never mentioned me.

150
00:09:14,818 --> 00:09:16,274
I didn't know him long.

151
00:09:16,968 --> 00:09:17,871
Maybe...

152
00:09:18,549 --> 00:09:19,934
What's your name?

153
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:21,688
Anna.

154
00:09:23,734 --> 00:09:25,484
I don't know what to say.

155
00:09:25,604 --> 00:09:27,944
I'm making good money, if that's...

156
00:09:28,658 --> 00:09:30,696
I know I owe you more than money.

157
00:09:32,986 --> 00:09:36,119
I have his purple heart
and his dog tags, if you want them.

158
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:40,059
He wanted to marry my sister.

159
00:09:41,370 --> 00:09:43,836
She looks just like me,
with two good legs.

160
00:09:48,252 --> 00:09:49,466
What is your name?

161
00:09:50,546 --> 00:09:51,802
Dick Whitman.

162
00:09:55,919 --> 00:09:57,516
What do I do with you?

163
00:10:07,937 --> 00:10:10,137
Well, this is a welcome surprise.

164
00:10:13,484 --> 00:10:14,919
I can come back.

165
00:10:15,039 --> 00:10:17,000
Oh no. Come. See this.

166
00:10:41,112 --> 00:10:43,365
I guess all you need
was an audience.

167
00:10:43,485 --> 00:10:44,605
Are you next?

168
00:10:45,295 --> 00:10:46,440
I don't play.

169
00:10:46,985 --> 00:10:49,527
- Teddy, this is my friend Dick.
- Hi.

170
00:10:50,041 --> 00:10:52,321
It's called, "The Hall
of the Mountain King."

171
00:10:53,003 --> 00:10:53,948
It's scary.

172
00:10:54,547 --> 00:10:55,470
I know.

173
00:10:56,277 --> 00:10:58,910
Take a lollipop.
I'll see you next week.

174
00:11:04,797 --> 00:11:06,212
Bye, Mrs. Draper.

175
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:09,921
You're tan.

176
00:11:11,037 --> 00:11:12,632
Are you here on vacation?

177
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:15,860
Business.

178
00:11:20,172 --> 00:11:21,435
You look good.

179
00:11:22,797 --> 00:11:24,347
Where are your things?

180
00:11:24,763 --> 00:11:27,071
Or are you just here for the day?

181
00:11:27,735 --> 00:11:29,685
I didn't even think about it.

182
00:11:31,987 --> 00:11:34,137
I didn't mean to intrude. I can...

183
00:11:34,674 --> 00:11:36,409
- Are you in trouble?
- No.

184
00:11:37,421 --> 00:11:38,771
Well, then, what?

185
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:43,949
Can I take a shower and lie down?

186
00:11:44,611 --> 00:11:45,611
Of course.

187
00:11:54,216 --> 00:11:55,362
You're late.

188
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:57,897
Spence-Chapin. How did that happen?

189
00:11:58,465 --> 00:12:01,868
I put us on the list. I don't know.
We went right to the top.

190
00:12:01,988 --> 00:12:04,117
Well, I'm not going,
and neither are you.

191
00:12:04,646 --> 00:12:06,760
- Peter, you're shouting.
- Don't do that.

192
00:12:07,047 --> 00:12:08,897
Listen to me very carefully.

193
00:12:09,798 --> 00:12:13,388
We are not adopting a child.

194
00:12:14,299 --> 00:12:15,421
That's final.

195
00:12:16,089 --> 00:12:17,181
Will you calm down,
and we can talk...

196
00:12:17,301 --> 00:12:19,157
Hell's bells, Trudy! That is final!

197
00:12:19,736 --> 00:12:21,576
You don't speak to me that way!

198
00:12:27,556 --> 00:12:29,292
You have lost your mind!

